  "title": "Question: hits template ng-href alternative?",
  "body": "Hello,\n\nIs it possible to use an href alternative in the hits templates? Like angular provides?\n\nSo for example instead of <a href=\"{{url}}\"></a> something like <a ng-href=\"{{url}}\"></a>? \n\nAsking this because some crawlers seem to follow the {{ url }} url of the template. \n",
